Financial institutions today face a rapidly increasing volume of fraudulent activities, including unauthorized credit card transactions and complex money laundering schemes.
With billions of transactions processed daily across multiple countries, detecting fraud in real time has become both a technical and regulatory necessity.
Many traditional banking systems rely on batch processing, meaning fraud is detected hours after it occurs. This delay increases financial losses and damages customer trust.
In addition, global banks must comply with strict anti-money laundering regulations. Failure to detect suspicious transactions can result in significant penalties and reputational harm.
Therefore, the bank needs a scalable, real-time architecture capable of detecting fraud instantly while ensuring full compliance with global AML regulations.
